      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROMAN CHARLIE (1) finished fourth last start over 1660m at this track, beaten 22 metres. Best recent result was a win at Ballarat three starts ago over 2200m. Likely to get all the favours from this nice draw. Beautifully placed and is sure to prove tough to beat. BETTOR BE BODHI (8) disappointed backers last time out when fifth, beaten 11 metres, over 1780m at Redcliffe. Form prior to that was solid, including a sound third over 1660m at this track two starts ago. Can travel in a nice spot from this draw and wait on the sprint lane if necessary. The recent run not a true indication. Good enough to take out a race like this. MALARKY (3) disappointed last time when eighth over 1660m at this track. Can make amends. RAINBOW FEELS (4) must be included on the back of some solid recent form, most recently when second at Redcliffe over 1780m.",
